        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 6:33PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 633 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Riverdale, or near
Jonesboro, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rain and slow moving storms may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Fayetteville, Jonesboro, City of South Fulton, Stockbridge,
Union City, Forest Park, Riverdale, College Park, Morrow, Hapeville,
Lake City, Hartsfield-Jackson Airport, Rex, Ellenwood, Hidden Valley
Park, Fort Gillem, Conley, Gresham Park, and Irondale.
</description>
        <instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
